Eli Carter scored 19 points to lead
 Rutgers University  to a 67-60 victory over eighth-ranked
University of Connecticut in college basketball.  Myles Mack came off the bench to score 14 points for the
Scarlett Knights, who shot 40 percent from the floor and 82
percent from the free-throw line at Louis Brown Athletic Center
in Piscataway,  New Jersey . They also hit seven of 18 3-pointers.  Shabazz Napier led the Huskies with 23 points and Andre
Drummond added 10 points and 12 rebounds. Connecticut connected
on 39 percent of its field goal attempts and 73 percent from the
foul line.  Rutgers improved to 9-7 overall and 1-2 in the Big East.
Connecticut, which lost its second straight game, fell to 12-3
and 2-2 in the  Big East .  To contact the reporter on this story:
